    <h1>Homemade Margherita Pizza</h1>

    <p>A classic Italian pizza featuring a thin, crispy crust topped with fresh tomato sauce, creamy mozzarella cheese, and aromatic basil leaves. It is the ultimate comfort food that brings a taste of Naples to your kitchen.</p>

    <h2>Ingredients</h2>

    <ul>
        <li>250g Pizza dough (store-bought or homemade)</li>
        <li>1/2 cup Tomato passata or crushed tomatoes</li>
        <li>150g Fresh mozzarella cheese, sliced or torn</li>
        <li>Fresh basil leaves</li>
        <li>1 tablespoon Extra virgin olive oil</li>
        <li>A pinch of salt and dried oregano</li>
        <li>Semolina or flour for dusting</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Method</h2>

    <ol>
        <li>Preheat your oven to its highest setting (usually 250°C/475°F) and place a pizza stone or baking tray inside to heat up.</li>
        <li>On a lightly floured surface, stretch or roll out the pizza dough into a 12-inch circle.</li>
        <li>Spread the tomato passata evenly over the dough, leaving a small border around the edge for the crust.</li>
        <li>Distribute the mozzarella slices evenly across the top and sprinkle with salt and dried oregano.</li>
        <li>Carefully transfer the pizza onto the preheated stone or tray in the oven.</li>
        <li>Bake for 8-10 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the cheese is bubbly and slightly charred.</li>
        <li>Remove from the oven, top with fresh basil leaves, and drizzle with extra virgin olive oil before serving.</li>
    </ol>

